  "text": "Effects of seed size restriction on GWASs We compared counts of significant genome-wide associations between the current sizecontrolled dataset and our previous study that did not control seed size [CITATION_1] . Both datasets were downsized to 160 accessions (representing the overlap of both studies). We compared cumulative counts from across 78 GWASs executed on 14 root morphology and two growth rate traits evaluated for five time points of a 5-d-long growth assay, four end points respectively for the 'rate' traits.",
